Greenview first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Greenview had a population of 208. The population density was {{convert|160.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Greenview was 162 (77.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.5%) [[African Americans|African American]], 7 (3.4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.5%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 7 (3.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 30 (14.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 22 persons (10.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Greenview CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0631134 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 82 households, out of which 9 (11.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 45 (54.9%) were married-couple households, 4 (4.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 12 (14.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 21 (25.6%) had a male householder with no partner present. 30 households (36.6%) were one person, and 17 (20.7%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.54.<ref name=DP1/> There were 47 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Greenview CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0631134 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 50 people (24.0%) under the age of 18, 4 people (1.9%) aged 18 to 24, 30 people (14.4%) aged 25 to 44, 58 people (27.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 66 people (31.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 51.0{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 82.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 98 housing units at an average density of {{convert|75.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 82 (83.7%) were occupied. Of these, 71 (86.6%) were owner-occupied, and 11 (13.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631134|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715025243/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631134|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Greenview CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Greenview had a population of 201. The population density was {{convert|145.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Greenview was 161 (80.1%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 10 (5.0%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1 (0.5%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 8 (4.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 21 (10.4%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 19 persons (9.5%).

The Census reported that 201 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 88 households, out of which 18 (20.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 51 (58.0%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 8 (9.1%) had a female householder with no husband present, 3 (3.4%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 4 (4.5%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (1.1%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 21 households (23.9%) were made up of individuals, and 9 (10.2%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.28.  There were 62 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (70.5% of all households); the average family size was 2.65.

The population was spread out, with 32 people (15.9%) under the age of 18, 13 people (6.5%) aged 18 to 24, 37 people (18.4%) aged 25 to 44, 80 people (39.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 39 people (19.4%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 52.6 years. For every 100 females, there were 97.1 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.3 males.

There were 100 housing units at an average density of {{convert|72.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 65 (73.9%) were owner-occupied, and 23 (26.1%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 1.5%; the rental vacancy rate was 4.0%.  155 people (77.1% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 46 people (22.9%) lived in rental housing units.

